@page "/help"
@attribute [ExcludeFromInteractiveRouting]

@using Anchor.Domain.Identity
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization

@attribute [Authorize]

<PageTitle>Help</PageTitle>

<section class="admin-page">
    <div class="page-hero page-hero--section">
        <p class="page-hero__eyebrow">Signed-In Help</p>
        <h1>Help</h1>
        <p class="page-hero__lead">
            This guide is only visible after sign-in and explains how the current role model, bootstrap flow,
            and staff onboarding process fit together.
        </p>
    </div>

    <StatusMessage />

    <div class="feature-grid">
        <article class="feature-card feature-card--tight">
            <p class="feature-card__eyebrow">Staff Workflow</p>
            <h3>Admins create staff accounts, then assign roles.</h3>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>An <strong>Admin</strong> creates each staff account and shares the temporary password with that employee directly.</li>
                <li>If a staff member forgets the current password, an <strong>Admin</strong> can set a fresh temporary password from <strong>User Management</strong>.</li>
                <li>If confirmed-account enforcement is enabled, the same <strong>Admin</strong> can confirm the account for sign-in from User Management even if the email address still has not been verified.</li>
                <li><strong>User Management</strong> also keeps each employee's profile details, such as name and phone number, up to date.</li>
                <li><strong>Manage Account</strong> lets each signed-in user update the same first name, last name, and phone number details for their own account.</li>
                <li>After the account exists, an <strong>Admin</strong> assigns only the operational or technical roles that person actually needs.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="feature-card feature-card--tight">
            <p class="feature-card__eyebrow">Role Summary</p>
            <h3>Keep responsibilities separated.</h3>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><strong>Admin</strong>: full access, user management, role assignment, and security settings.</li>
                <li><strong>EventManager</strong>: event-related administration only.</li>
                <li><strong>MenuManager</strong>: menu-related administration only.</li>
                <li><strong>IT</strong>: technical and system-facing functionality.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="feature-card feature-card--tight">
            <p class="feature-card__eyebrow">Bootstrap Safety</p>
            <h3>Use the seed account only to get the site operational.</h3>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>The app seeds required roles automatically on startup.</li>
                <li>The bootstrap user stops seeding once the system has at least one <strong>Admin</strong> and one <strong>IT</strong> user.</li>
                <li>The seeded password must be changed before that account can open the rest of the site.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="feature-card feature-card--tight">
            <p class="feature-card__eyebrow">Confirmed Accounts</p>
            <h3>Configuration controls the live rule.</h3>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>The fallback value lives in <code>appsettings.json</code>.</li>
                <li>An environment variable can override the live behavior.</li>
                <li>Account confirmation controls sign-in approval separately from whether the current email address has been verified.</li>
                <li>The Security page shows both the effective value and the fallback file value.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>
    </div>

    <AuthorizeView Policy="@ApplicationPolicies.AdminAccess">
        <section class="admin-card">
            <div class="admin-card__header">
                <h2>Admin pages</h2>
                <span class="admin-card__badge">Staff setup</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><strong>User Management</strong> is where you maintain staff profile details, confirm account access, reset forgotten passwords with a new temporary password, and add or remove roles.</li>
                <li><strong>Manage Account</strong> is where each signed-in user updates their own first name, last name, and phone number.</li>
                <li><strong>Security</strong> is where you update the fallback confirmed-account setting and review bootstrap coverage.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </AuthorizeView>
</section>
